From 928362b5f51000a31a94171b45c9e4aaefa26ce5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 11:58:52 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): journal state snapshots with crash-safe
 compaction (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add a versioned state_snapshot journal event and seed replay from the
latest valid snapshot in the existing run-journal.ts replayer (single
source of replay truth); refuse unsupported snapshot versions naming the
journal path. Compaction follows a crash-safe protocol (tmp snapshot →
fsync → one-generation journal.jsonl.bak → atomic rename) with crash
injection tested at every intermediate point, and refuses active runs or
journals that do not replay cleanly. The engine auto-compacts at
node-completion boundaries via defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events
(0 disables; default 500); manual compaction ships as
`flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <id> [--dry-run]`.

Docs: FR-E83 (SRS 01-execution-model + indexes), SDS journal/recovery
contract split into design-engine/04a-journal-recovery.md, README
configuration + CLI help.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
