+<!-- section file — index: [documents/design-engine.md](../design-engine.md) -->
+
+# SDS Engine — Journal & Recovery Contract
+
+Split out of [04-data-and-logic.md](04-data-and-logic.md) §5 Logic
+(token-budget split). Owns the `journal.jsonl` recovery contract.
+
+## Durable Lifecycle Replay (FR-E69)
+
+`run-journal.ts` owns the recovery surface. Writer appends enveloped JSON
+lines with monotonic `seq` and deterministic `event_id`, continuing after
+existing valid records on resume. Fresh runs write ordinary bootstrap facts,
+not a snapshot blob. Replay reads only the run directory, ignores duplicate
+`event_id`s and a malformed partial tail, fails on malformed non-tail lines,
+and derives `RunState`. Terminal records beat stale non-terminal run facts;
+later terminal facts can supersede earlier ones. Dashboard and resume replay
+the journal rather than `state.json`.
+
+## Journal Snapshots + Crash-Safe Compaction (FR-E83)
+
+- **Snapshot event:** `state_snapshot` = `{ snapshot_version: 1, state:
+  <complete replayed RunState — run status/metadata, per-node statuses and
+  facts, declared nodes, costs>, events_covered }`, enveloped like every
+  journal line. Written exclusively by compaction.
+- **Replay:** the same `run-journal.ts` replayer (single source of replay
+  truth) seeds from the LATEST valid snapshot via `structuredClone` and
+  applies only events after it. Snapshotless journals replay exactly as
+  before. `snapshot_version > SUPPORTED_SNAPSHOT_VERSION` fails replay with
+  an error naming the journal path and the version — never silently skipped
+  or partially applied. Torn-trailing-line tolerance keeps working on
+  compacted journals, including a torn line directly after the snapshot.
+- **Compaction protocol (exact order):** (1) replay the current journal;
+  (2) write `journal.jsonl.tmp` containing one `state_snapshot` event and
+  zero tail events; (3) fsync the tmp file; (4) copy the current journal to
+  `journal.jsonl.bak` (exactly one generation kept); (5) atomically rename
+  tmp over `journal.jsonl`. The rename is the only mutation of
+  `journal.jsonl`, so a crash at any intermediate point leaves the old
+  journal intact and replayable. A test-only `faultHook` injects crashes
+  between consecutive steps.
+- **Refusals (nothing modified):** run is active — the workflow lock names
+  this run id and its PID is alive (`isRunLive`) — or the journal does not
+  replay cleanly beyond the standard torn-line tolerance.
+- **Engine auto-compaction:** `RunJournalWriter` tracks
+  `eventsSinceSnapshot`; `Engine.executeNode` checks it at node-completion
+  boundaries ONLY (never mid-node) against
+  `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events` (non-negative integer; `0`
+  disables; default 500) and calls `writer.compact()` — snapshot `seq`
+  allocated from the writer's own counter so later appends stay monotonic.
+  Emits one `journal compacted: …` status line.
+- **CLI:** `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <id>
+  [--dry-run]` via shared `compactRun()` (adds run-not-found and active-run
+  guards). Success prints exactly
+  `compacted <runId>: <eventsBefore> -> <eventsAfter> events,
+  <bytesBefore> -> <bytesAfter> bytes (backup: journal.jsonl.bak)`;
+  `--dry-run` computes counts/bytes without writing; errors are one line,
+  exit 1, never a stack trace.
