+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal State Snapshots and Crash-Safe Compaction
+
+- **Description:** The run journal format supports a `state_snapshot` event
+  carrying `snapshot_version: 1`, the complete replayed run model (run
+  status/metadata, per-node statuses and facts, declared nodes, costs), and
+  `events_covered`. The existing replayer in `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+  remains the single source of replay truth: when a journal contains
+  snapshots, replay seeds from the LATEST valid snapshot and applies only
+  events after it; journals without snapshots replay exactly as before; a
+  snapshot with `snapshot_version` greater than supported fails replay with
+  an error naming the journal path and the version. Compaction follows a
+  crash-safe protocol — replay → write `journal.jsonl.tmp` (one snapshot
+  event) → fsync tmp → copy journal to `journal.jsonl.bak` (one generation
+  kept) → atomic rename — so a crash at any intermediate point leaves a
+  replayable journal. Compaction refuses when the run is active (its lock is
+  held by a live process) or the journal does not replay cleanly beyond the
+  torn-line tolerance. The engine auto-compacts at node-completion
+  boundaries only (never mid-node) when events since the last snapshot
+  exceed `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events` (non-negative
+  integer; `0` disables; default 500), reporting one status line. Manual
+  compaction: `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId>
+  [--dry-run]` with an exact one-line summary mentioning the backup.
+- **Tasks:** [REF:task:2026-06-journal-snapshot-compaction | journal-snapshot-compaction]
+- **Motivation:** Long runs grow `journal.jsonl` without bound and replay
+  cost grows with it (FR-E69 explicitly deferred compaction). Snapshots
+  truncate the replay prefix without weakening the durability contract.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts` (FR-E83;
+    regression-locked; snapshot seeding from the latest snapshot, forward
+    version refusal naming path+version, compacted vs full replay JSON byte
+    equality, suffix-only replay by line/parse counting, torn line after
+    snapshot, crash injection at every protocol point, both refusal cases,
+    one-generation backup, boundary-only auto-trigger with one verbose
+    line, threshold `0` disables), `src/config/config_test.ts` +
+    `src/config/merge_defaults_test.ts` (threshold validation + drift),
+    `src/cli_test.ts` (FR-E83; `runs compact` parsing, exact summary line,
+    `--dry-run` no-op, run-not-found/refusal exit codes, `--help` listing).
+  - Evidence: `deno task check`.
