+# engine: Journal snapshots with crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Bound `journal.jsonl` growth and replay cost without weakening the FR-E69
+durability contract: add a `state_snapshot` journal event, seed replay from
+the latest snapshot, and provide a crash-safe compaction operation —
+automatic in the engine at node-completion boundaries and manual via
+`flowai-workflow runs compact`.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+FR-E69 made `journal.jsonl` the sole recovery surface: an append-only JSONL
+stream replayed from an empty in-memory model. That task explicitly deferred
+snapshots/compaction ("linear replay accepted... compaction not part of the
+design unless a future task demonstrates a measured need"). Long runs now
+demonstrate that need: the journal grows without bound and replay cost grows
+with it. This task supersedes the FR-E69 "no embedded snapshot records"
+constraint with a versioned, refusal-guarded snapshot format.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` — `RunJournalWriter` (append, seq continuity,
+  torn-tail truncation on open) and `replayRunJournal()` (dedup by
+  `event_id`, torn-trailing-line tolerance, malformed-non-tail failure,
+  `applyJournalEvents` building `RunState`).
+- `src/types.ts` — `RunJournalEventKind` union, per-kind event interfaces,
+  `RunJournalReplayResult { state, events, ignored_duplicate_event_ids,
+  ignored_partial_tail }`.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` — per-workflow lock at `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock`;
+  `isRunLive(workflowDir, runId)` reports live-PID ownership for a run.
+- `src/engine/engine.ts` — opens the writer per run, emits bootstrap facts,
+  drives node completion via `nodeCompleted()` in `executeNode`.
+- `src/config/config.ts` — `DEFAULT_WORKFLOW_DEFAULTS`, `validateSchema`
+  defaults-section validation (FR-E7 drift detection locks this in
+  `config_test.ts`; `merge_defaults_test.ts` guards workflow-only defaults
+  from leaking into per-node settings).
+- `src/cli.ts` — subcommand dispatch (`run`/`answer`/`init`/`mcp`), exported
+  arg parsers unit-tested in `src/cli_test.ts`, `printUsage()` help.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- The EXISTING replayer in `src/state/run-journal.ts` stays the single
+  source of replay truth — extend it; a second replayer is forbidden.
+- Follow the `src/cli.ts` argument-parsing style; no new dependencies.
+- Reuse `getRunDir`/`getJournalPath`/`defaultLockPath`; no duplicated path
+  construction.
+- Tests live alongside their subsystems: journal/replay + compaction +
+  engine auto-trigger tests in `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts`;
+  config validation/drift in `src/config/config_test.ts` +
+  `src/config/merge_defaults_test.ts`; CLI in `src/cli_test.ts`.
+- Plain JSONL stays; exactly one `.bak` generation; no batch compaction.
+- `deno task check` stays green.
+
+### Key design decisions
+
+- **Snapshot payload** carries `snapshot_version: 1`, `state` (the complete
+  replayed `RunState` — run status/metadata, per-node statuses and facts,
+  declared nodes, costs; this is everything `applyJournalEvents`
+  reconstructs into the replay result's run model), and `events_covered`
+  (unique events + ignored duplicates subsumed).
+- **Equivalence invariant (item 6)** is asserted on the replay results' run
+  model: `JSON.stringify(replay(full).state)` byte-equals
+  `JSON.stringify(replay(snapshot + tail).state)`. The `events` array of a
+  compacted journal cannot equal the original by construction — item 7
+  mandates the pre-snapshot history be physically gone from the file.
+- **Forward refusal**: any snapshot with `snapshot_version` greater than the
+  supported version fails replay with an error naming the journal path and
+  the version — checked for every snapshot before seeding.
+- **Seq continuity**: the live engine compacts through
+  `RunJournalWriter.compact()`, which allocates the snapshot's `seq` from
+  the writer's own counter — no seq/event_id collisions with subsequent
+  appends. CLI compaction (no live writer) derives `seq = maxSeq + 1` from
+  the replayed events.
+- **Active-run refusal**: the shared `compactRun()` entry (used by the CLI)
+  refuses when `isRunLive(workflowDir, runId)` — the run's lock is held by a
+  live process. Engine auto-compaction calls `writer.compact()` directly:
+  the engine IS the live lock holder, so the refusal rule does not apply to
+  its own in-run compaction (it compacts at a quiescent node boundary while
+  holding the lock).
+- **Threshold**: `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events`
+  (workflow-level setting, sibling of `max_parallel`): non-negative integer,
+  `0` = auto-compaction disabled, default `500` (a few node lifecycles plus
+  attempt/loop facts per node keeps typical journals to tens of events per
+  node; 500 compacts long loop-heavy runs every handful of iterations while
+  keeping compaction I/O negligible).
+- **Boundary-only trigger**: checked in `Engine.executeNode` immediately
+  after a successful top-level `nodeCompleted` — never mid-node; loop body
+  completions happen inside the enclosing loop node and do not trigger.
+
