+## Solution
+
+Selected variant: **V2 — extend `run-journal.ts` as the single replay/compaction
+authority** (see Variant Analysis below; V1 risks a second replayer and seq
+collisions; V3 exceeds the task's explicit out-of-scope list).
+
+### Files to modify
+
+1. `src/types.ts`
+   - Add `"state_snapshot"` to `RunJournalEventKind`.
+   - Add `StateSnapshotJournalEvent extends RunJournalEventBase` with
+     `kind: "state_snapshot"`, `snapshot_version: number` (writer always
+     emits `1`; typed `number` so replay can inspect forward versions),
+     `state: RunState`, `events_covered: number`; add to `RunJournalEvent`
+     union.
+   - Add `journal_compaction_threshold_events?: number` to
+     `WorkflowDefaults` (workflow-only field, like `max_parallel`).
+2. `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+   - `SUPPORTED_SNAPSHOT_VERSION = 1` exported const.
+   - `applyJournalEvents(events, journalPath)`: pre-scan for snapshots —
+     throw on any `snapshot_version > SUPPORTED_SNAPSHOT_VERSION` (error
+     names `journalPath` and the version); seed `state` from a deep clone of
+     the LATEST snapshot's `state` and apply only subsequent events.
+   - `RunJournalWriter`: track `#eventsSinceSnapshot` (initialized in
+     `open()` from parsed events after the last snapshot; incremented per
+     `append`), expose readonly getter; add `compact(opts?)` that runs the
+     shared protocol with `seq` from the writer's counter and resets the
+     counter.
+   - Crash-safe protocol helper (shared by writer + CLI path), exact order:
+     (1) `replayRunJournal(runDir)`; (2) write
+     `journal.jsonl.tmp` = one enveloped `state_snapshot` line; (3) fsync
+     tmp (`Deno.FsFile.sync`); (4) `Deno.copyFile` journal →
+     `journal.jsonl.bak`; (5) `Deno.rename` tmp → `journal.jsonl`.
+     `faultHook?(point)` invoked between consecutive steps with points
+     `after_replay | after_tmp_write | after_tmp_fsync | after_backup`
+     (test-only crash injection).
+   - `compactRun({ workflowDir, runId, dryRun?, faultHook? })`: resolves
+     `getRunDir`/`getJournalPath`, errors clearly when the journal is
+     missing (run not found), refuses when `isRunLive(workflowDir, runId)`
+     (lock held by live process) or when replay fails beyond torn-line
+     tolerance (wrapped "Compaction refused" error, nothing modified);
+     `dryRun` computes the summary (event counts, byte sizes) without
+     writing. Returns `CompactionSummary { runId, eventsBefore, eventsAfter,
+     bytesBefore, bytesAfter, backupPath }`.
+3. `src/config/config.ts`
+   - `DEFAULT_WORKFLOW_DEFAULTS.journal_compaction_threshold_events: 500`.
+   - `validateSchema` defaults section: reject non-integer or negative
+     values (style of `validateWallClockBudget`; `0` accepted = disabled).
+4. `src/engine/engine.ts`
+   - In `executeNode`, after the successful `nodeCompleted(...)` branch
+     (node-completion boundary, never mid-node): if resolved threshold > 0
+     and `journal.eventsSinceSnapshot > threshold`, `await journal.compact()`
+     and emit ONE `output.status("engine", ...)` line naming the run and
+     before→after event counts.
+5. `src/cli.ts`
+   - `parseRunsCompactArgs(args)` exported (style of `parseAnswerArgs`):
+     `--workflow <dir>`/`--workflow=`, `--run <id>`/`--run=`, `--dry-run`;
+     `--workflow` falls back to `resolveActiveWorkflow` (FR-E78 rule).
+   - `runsCompactCommand(args)` exported testable core returning
+     `{ code, stdout, stderr }`; success prints EXACTLY
+     `compacted <runId>: <eventsBefore> -> <eventsAfter> events,
+     <bytesBefore> -> <bytesAfter> bytes (backup: journal.jsonl.bak)`;
+     dry-run prints a `dry-run:` prefixed line with the same counts and
+     modifies nothing; errors are one line, exit code 1, no stack trace.
+   - Dispatch `runs` subcommand (`compact` sub-action) in
+     `import.meta.main`; add to `printUsage()`.
+6. `src/mod.ts` — export `compactRun`, `CompactionSummary`,
+   `SUPPORTED_SNAPSHOT_VERSION`, `CompactionFaultPoint`, and
+   `StateSnapshotJournalEvent` type for embedding hosts.
+7. Tests (TDD per step): `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts`,
+   `src/config/config_test.ts`, `src/config/merge_defaults_test.ts`,
+   `src/cli_test.ts` — cases listed in the DoD.
+8. Documentation:
+   - `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`: new FR-E83
+     section (durability/recovery) with Description, Motivation,
+     Acceptance (test refs above).
+   - `documents/requirements-engine.md`: FR-E83 index row → 01-execution-model.
+   - `documents/index.md`: FR-E83 row under `## FR`.
+   - `documents/design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md`: extend the Run Journal
+     entity bullet and the "Durable Lifecycle Replay (FR-E69)" logic section
+     with snapshot format, replay seeding, forward refusal, and the 5-step
+     compaction protocol + threshold setting.
+   - `README.md`: `journal_compaction_threshold_events` bullet in the
+     Configuration defaults list; `runs compact` in the CLI section.
+
+### Error handling strategy
+
+Compaction never half-applies: every failure before the atomic rename leaves
+`journal.jsonl` untouched (tmp/bak files are inert leftovers, overwritten on
+the next attempt). Replay errors and refusals surface as thrown `Error`s
+with actionable messages; the CLI maps them to a one-line stderr message and
+exit 1. Journal append/compaction failures inside the engine propagate (fail
+fast — same policy as journal appends today).
+
+### Verification commands
+
+- `deno task test src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts`
+- `deno task test src/config/config_test.ts src/config/merge_defaults_test.ts`
+- `deno task test src/cli_test.ts`
+- `deno task check`
+
+## Variant Analysis (recorded; non-interactive selection)
+
+- **V1 Quick fix** — standalone compactor module with its own journal IO and
+  seq bookkeeping. Pros: zero churn in `run-journal.ts`. Cons: gravitates
+  toward a second replay implementation (violates item 4); live-writer seq
+  collisions after in-run compaction. Risks: divergence of replay semantics.
+  Best for: one-off offline tooling — not this task.
+- **V2 Architecturally correct (SELECTED)** — extend the existing replayer +
+  writer; shared protocol core; CLI wrapper with refusal rules. Pros: single
+  replay truth, seq continuity, all 15 items satisfied without scope creep.
+  Cons: `run-journal.ts` grows (still within file budget). Risks: low.
+- **V3 Best long-term** — generalized checkpoint subsystem (multi-generation
+  retention, batch/cross-run compaction, pluggable retention policy). Pros:
+  future-proof. Cons: explicitly out of scope (one `.bak`, no batch); higher
+  complexity with no current consumer.
+- Trade-offs: V2 keeps complexity proportional to the durability guarantee;
+  V3 trades simplicity for unneeded generality; V1 trades correctness risk
+  for speed. Selection rationale: V2 is the only variant satisfying the hard
+  single-replayer requirement without overbuilding.
+
+## Follow-ups (deferred)
+
+- Multi-generation backup retention / configurable retention policy.
+- Snapshot-aware `list_runs` MCP fast path (replay already benefits).
+- Compaction metrics in the run summary.
+- Pre-existing staleness: README architecture mermaid + workflow-folder tree
+  still reference `state.json` (removed by FR-E69) — out-of-scope here.
